After seeing how this daily practice affected my photography, I tried it on my
writing, aiming for 250 words every day on a subject. As with my daily photo, I
just had to try. The subject didn't have to be thought-provoking, just
cohesive, and I spent only a short time on edits. I managed to keep that up for two weeks before stumbling.

Although I didn't intend to take it on as practice, within the past few years I
started doing crosswords every day on the way to work. Easy ones in the daily
commuter local at first, then more challenging ones from the bigger papers. It
didn't take long for me to consistently finish a crossword on my 45-minute
commute. Nowadays, I can finish a crossword in the commuter dailies in less
than 15 minutes — thanks to a little practice every day.

